m at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh Hollynshed was born about 1250, in Sutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Hollynshed."},"et":{"about 1250–":"umbes 1250–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1279":"1279","about 1279":"umbes 1279","1250":"1250","Sutton, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1250–":"noin 1250–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","1279":"1279","about 1279":"noin 1279","1250":"1250","Sutton, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1250–":"environ 1250–Décédé","1250–Female":"1250–Décédée","1279–Female":"1279–Décédée","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","about 1250":"environ 1250","1279":"1279","about 1279":"environ 1279","1250":"1250","Sutton, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Hugh Hollynshed est né environ 1250, à Sutton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Hollynshed."},"de":{"about 1250–":"um 1250–Verstorben","1250–Female":"1250–Verstorben","1279–Female":"1279–Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","about 1250":"um 1250","1279":"1279","about 1279":"um 1279","1250":"1250","Sutton, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Sutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Hugh Hollynshed wurde um 1250 in Sutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mit Hollynshed mindestens 1 To